JEDDAH: The first group of Hajj 2022 pilgrims to arrive through Jeddah Islamic Port were welcomed to the Kingdom on Thursday.   The group came from Sudan and had their entry procedures completed with ease, Saudi Press Agency reported.   The General Directorate of Passports confirmed its readiness to receive pilgrims and visitors to the two holy mosques by supporting its platforms with modern technical devices and qualified employees to complete entry procedures.